<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Frey Root CA Installation</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: "Inter", "Segoe UI", sans-serif; background-color: #0d1117; color: #f1f5f9; margin: 0; padding: 2rem; line-height: 1.5; }
    a { color: #4ade80; }
    h1, h2 { margin-top: 0; }
    .card { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(15,23,42,0.35); }
    ol, ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
    code { background: rgba(15,23,42,0.8); padding: 0.15rem 0.35rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .guide h3 { margin-top: 0; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Frey Root Certificate Authority</h1>
  <p>Install the Frey private CA on every device before visiting <code>*.{{ network.domain_name }}</code> services. This avoids HTTPS warnings and ensures trusted TLS for Traefik, Authentik, and every self-hosted application.</p>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Download</h2>
    <p>Always download the certificate directly from your Frey host:</p>
    <p><strong>File:</strong> <a href="/assets/{{ landing_page.certificate.download_name }}">{{ landing_page.certificate.download_name }}</a></p>
    <p>SHA-256: <code>Run openssl sha256 {{ landing_page.certificate.download_name }} to verify</code></p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Why install the CA?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Enables trusted HTTPS for <code>https://frey</code> and every <code>https://service.{{ network.domain_name }}</code> endpoint.</li>
      <li>Allows mobile apps (Home Assistant, Immich, Jellyfin, etc.) to sync without certificate prompts.</li>
      <li>Powers mutual trust for Authentik OIDC callbacks and API clients.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

{% for guide in landing_page.certificate_guides %}
  <div class="card guide" id="{{ guide.slug }}">
    <h3>{{ guide.title }}</h3>
    <ol>
{% for step in guide.steps %}
      <li>{{ step }}</li>
{% endfor %}
    </ol>
    <p><strong>Verify:</strong></p>
    <ul>
{% for verify in guide.verify %}
      <li>{{ verify }}</li>
{% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
{% endfor %}

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Browsers cache trust for a few minutes; restart the browser if warnings persist.</li>
      <li>Android requires a screen lock before user CA certificates can be added.</li>
      <li>On Linux, confirm trust with <code>trust list | grep "Frey Root"</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
